DATA TYPES
Labeled vs Unlabeled Data
Labeled Data
Data that comes with the "answer key" or target variable.
Example:

// Labeled dataset for spam detection
[
  { email: "Win money now!!!", label: "spam" },           // ← Label
  { email: "Meeting at 3pm", label: "not_spam" },         // ← Label
  { email: "Claim your prize", label: "spam" }            // ← Label
]

Real-world analogy:
Like a database where every record has a category_id or status field already filled in.
Unlabeled Data
Data without answers/tags.
Example:

// Unlabeled dataset
[
  { email: "Win money now!!!" },
  { email: "Meeting at 3pm" },
  { email: "Claim your prize" }
  // No labels! Just raw data.
]

Real-world analogy:
Like a raw log file with no categorization — just pure data.
Structured vs Unstructured Data
Structured Data
Organized, tabular data with clear schema.
Examples:
SQL database tables
CSV files
Excel spreadsheets
JSON with fixed schema

-- Structured data (PostgreSQL table)
CREATE TABLE users (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    age INTEGER,
    email VARCHAR(100)
);


Unstructured Data
No predefined format or organization.
Examples:
Text documents (emails, articles)
Images
Audio files
Videos
Social media posts
Real-world analogy:
Structured = Your Prisma schema with defined models
Unstructured = A folder of random PDFs, images, and text files
🔗 How Data Types Connect to ML Learning Types

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    ML LEARNING TYPES                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                          │
│  SUPERVISED LEARNING                                     │
│  ├─ Uses: LABELED data                                   │
│  ├─ Can use: Structured OR Unstructured                  │
│  └─ Example: Spam detection (labeled emails)             │
│                                                          │
│  UNSUPERVISED LEARNING                                   │
│  ├─ Uses: UNLABELED data                                 │
│  ├─ Can use: Structured OR Unstructured                  │
│  └─ Example: Customer segmentation (no labels)           │
│                                                          │
│  SELF-SUPERVISED LEARNING                                │
│  ├─ Uses: UNLABELED data (creates own labels)            │
│  ├─ Mostly: Unstructured (text, images)                  │
│  └─ Example: Predicting next word in sentence            │
│                                                          │
│  REINFORCEMENT LEARNING                                  │
│  ├─ Uses: Rewards/penalties (not traditional labels)     │
│  ├─ Learns from: Interaction with environment            │
│  └─ Example: AI learning to play chess                   │
│                                                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
